  "title": "docs(storybook): integrate storybook example to our docs",
  "body": "This PR contains the inclusion of the storybook examples inside our doc. \n- I voluntarily let localhost url because our online docs is very old. I thought it might be better for designing to see the actual stuff. Unfortunately, you'll need to run `npm run storybook` on top of `npm run start` for now. Do you think it worth to try to have two url (dev & prod) ? \n\nThis PR also includes: \n- Fix a bug on the Pagination widget.\n- Removing duplicate widgets such as RefinementListLinks and so on.\n- Some fix about new props name (items, currentRefinement and stuff).\n\n![storybook-inside-docs](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6885378/19688078/5dc6d29a-9ac8-11e6-90b6-32803895802f.gif)\n",
